=========================

Published on Nov 10, 2014
Fiat and Chrysler approach building a "driver's car" in two very different ways. The new Dodge Viper TA is latest honing of an idea that started in 1992. Big engine, RWD, old school, if you will. 

The Alfa Romeo 4C is a new recipe: carbon fiber tub, small force-fed engine, AWD. 

Where should you spend your money? Which is the most rewarding, and the most fun? Mike Musto and Matt Farah went to Northern California to find out
